CounterStrike-1K Release Artifacts License

Released artifacts (rendered POV video and audio, packed action and state
sidecars, sparse event sidecars, public metadata, indices, schema files,
manifests, and aggregate statistics) are provided under the Creative Commons
Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International License (CC BY-NC 4.0) to the
extent of the authors' rights.

Full license text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/legalcode

Source code in this repository (Python loader, examples, training utilities)
is also released under CC BY-NC 4.0 to keep the artifact and tooling licenses
aligned for non-commercial research.

Counter-Strike 2 and underlying game assets (maps, models, textures, audio,
engine, and game content) remain the property of Valve Corporation. The
public artifacts in this release are derived rendered material and do not
redistribute the underlying game files.

Raw HLTV demo files are not redistributed. Public artifacts contain no Steam
IDs, online account identifiers, raw HLTV identifiers, profile URLs, player
names, or chat text. The anonymized identifier pov_idx is only stable within
a single match.

Out-of-scope uses:
- Commercial use of the rendered artifacts or derived models
- Re-identifying players or linking players across matches
- Recovering Steam IDs or online accounts
- Player profiling, ranking, anti-cheat, or surveillance use cases
